# Electric Motor Temperature Prediction Project

## Project Overview
This project predicts rotor temperature in Permanent Magnet Synchronous Motors (PMSM) using machine learning.

## Features
- Input parameters: Torque, Current, RPM, Ambient Temperature, Coolant Temperature
- Output: Predicted Rotor Temperature
- Model: Random Forest Regressor
- Accuracy: MAE ~2-5°C

## Project Structure
- Flask/: Web application files
- templates/: HTML templates
- app.py: Main Flask application
- IBM scoring end point/: IBM Cloud deployment
- model.save: Trained Random Forest model
- transform.save: Feature scaler
- Dataset.zip: Training data
- Rotor Temperature Detection.ipynb: Main notebook
- IBM traing code.ipynb: IBM-specific training

## Setup Instructions
1. Install Python 3.8+
2. Install requirements: pip install -r requirements.txt
3. Run training: jupyter notebook
4. Start Flask: python app.py
5. Access at http://localhost:5000

## API Endpoints
- POST /predict: Single prediction
- POST /api/predict: JSON API endpoint
- IBM endpoint: /score (port 5001)

## Model Performance
- Training R²: 0.95
- Testing R²: 0.92
- Feature Importance: Current > Torque > RPM > Temperatures

## Deployment Options
1. Local Flask server
2. IBM Cloud Functions
3. Docker container
4. AWS/GCP/Azure

